               <span class="bodySubtitle">Software Design Engineer</span><br/>
               Business Unit Description: Motorola Canada Software Center
               <br><br>
               The Motorola Canada Software Center (MCSC) is part of Motorola's Global Software Group (GSG). GSG's mandate is to provide software development services to all the Motorola product groups. 
               <br><br>
               MCSC develops software on a wide range of products and platforms. MCSC adheres to a well defined software development process and has successfully achieved the SEI CMM Level 5 certification.
               <br><br>
               Some of the project work that is currently underway in the centre includes :
               
               <ul class="bodyText">
               <li>Development of enhanced functionality for the two way radio infrastructure that is used by public safety (police and fire departments)</li>
               <li>Tools to configure the cellular subscriber units</li>
               <li>Tools to configure the network elements of Motorola cellular and two way radio infrastructure</li>
               <li>Software applications for public safety that utilize the wireless communications networks.</li>
               <li>Test and load tools for various network elements (cellular and two way radio)</li>
               </ul>
               
               Software projects are executed by teams ranging in size from 2 to 30 engineers led by a Project Manager. Duties that project team members are expected to perform are described below.
               <br><br>
               Design and develop software applications for use on the Windows and/or embedded platforms for various Motorola products.<br>
               Participate in different software production processes (analysis, design, coding, testing).<br>
               Ability to work effectively in a team environment or on individual assignments<br>
               Ability to work to deadlines<br>
               Ability to communicate effectively verbally and in written English<br>
               Candidates must be flexible, willing to learn, analytical, detail-oriented, and able to work independently.<br>
               <br><br>
               Software development experience in one or more of the following areas :<br>
               Windows Platform<br>
               Essential:<br>
               Experience developing Windows applications with Visual C++, and Java.<br>
               Programming experience with ATL and/or MFC frameworks including GUI design and usage of 3rd-party libraries would be an asset.<br>
               Knowledge of object-oriented methodology and some understanding of DCOM/COM technology.<br>
               Essential: Strong knowledge in C# and .NET<br>
               Some knowledge of core Windows technologies (such as windows services, Win32 IPC, Active Directory, MSMQ, etc.) and of one or more communication protocols (such as TCP/IP, RPC, SNMP, SMTP) would be an asset.<br>
               <br><br>
               General Software Development Skills<br>
               Knowledge of scripting tools such as Perl/VBscript/TCL Web-design/development<br>
               Data Structures<br>
               Database<br>
               Object Oriented principles<br>
               </ul>
